                            <comment id="249706" author="simmonsja" created="Sat, 22 Jun 2019 23:55:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Is this still true now that &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/33894&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/33894&lt;/a&gt;&#160;landed?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="246560" author="adilger" created="Tue, 30 Apr 2019 18:38:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This looks like a test script problem because it is checking for &lt;tt&gt;-ffff&lt;/tt&gt; in the OSC name which is x86 specific. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
